'''Relapsing–remitting''' is a medical term referring to a presentation of disease [[symptom]]s that become worse over time ([[Relapse|relapsing]]), followed by periods of less severe symptoms that do not completely cease ([[Remittance|remitting]]).  The term is sometimes applied to groupings of presentations of particular diseases that display this pattern, such as:

* [[Multiple sclerosis#Types|Relapsing–remitting multiple sclerosis]]

